race.comment: KERMA ART (8) backs up quickly after finishing in the money at Adaminaby. Faces a wide draw but gets the key booking of McDougall, which could prove decisive. Ready to break a long run of outs. JINGU EXPRESS (2) has found form with wins in her last two. Not that much tougher this time but will carry more weight. Have to take seriously. DON'T TELL SHERIFF (10) steps up in trip after a strong second at Hay seven days ago. That run suggested he's close to a win and he should go well again. STRUMMER (1) was well fancied at Tumut last time but found one better, beaten narrowly. With a month between runs and rising in trip, he looks a genuine threat. PATRICK (11) has been in the market recently without delivering, his latest a modest sixth at Wodonga. Capable of better and worth including.
